us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame

Class FramePose2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.FramePose2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Pose2DBasics, Pose2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.EpsilonComparable<FramePose2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometricallyComparable<FramePose2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FramePose2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Settable<FramePose2D>, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, FixedFramePose2DBasics, FrameChangeable, FramePose2DBasics, FramePose2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder

    public class FramePose2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements FramePose2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.GeometryObject<FramePose2D>
    FramePose2D is a 2D pose expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Pose2DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FramePose2D. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on poses occur in the same coordinate system. Also, via the method FrameChangeable.changeFrame(ReferenceFrame), one can easily calculates the value of a point in different reference frames.

    Because a FramePose2D extends Pose2DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Pose2DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FramePose2D.
